BY SANDRA BENEDICT
 
The Governor of Ekiti State, Ayodele Fayose, recalled six out of the 16 dismissed commissioners.

The governor in a major decision, dissolved the state executive council last week.

He however, in a statement by Lere Olayinka, his Special Assistant on Public Communications and New Media, on Sunday directed the recall commissioners to return to their duty post on Monday (today).

Those recalled are Ayodele Michael; Commissioner for Commerce and Industry.

ALSO SEE: What Tony Tetuila’s new look says about his political career

Commissioner for Environment, Bisi Kolawole; Mrs Funmi Ogun Commissioner for works, Kehinde Odebunmi Commissioner for Agriculture, Toyin Ojo (Finance) and Dr Olurotimi Ojo, Commissioner for Health).

The statement went further to explain that the remaining 10 commissioners shall be appointed in due course, calling on the people of the state to be patient.

The governor also promised to give the people the deserved dividends of democracy by raising a good team that will ensure this.
